{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-js","path":"/post/ternyata-musik-tradisional-indonesia-bisa-dipadukan-dengan-kesenian-jepang-loh/","result":{"data":{"wordpressPost":{"title":"Ternyata Musik Tradisional Indonesia Bisa Dipadukan dengan Kesenian Jepang, Loh!","content":"<p>Hayo, bro sis yang kemarin hadir di acara Bonenkai ke 12 di Hotel Salak Heritage Bogor tunjuk tangan! Kalian pasti setujukan acara yang diselenggarakan oleh Sekolah Tinggi Pariwisata Bogor (STP Bogor) dan Lembaga Keterampilan dan Pelatihan – Bogor Hospitality Initiative (LKP-BHI) ini seru banget dan pastinya memberikan kesan tersendiri. Karena Bonenkai Festival sendiri pada hakikatnya memiliki tujuan untuk membuang rasa lelah dan ketegangan selama setahun berlalu.</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_41739\" style=\"width: 618px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-41739\" data-attachment-id=\"41739\" data-permalink=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/news/ternyata-musik-tradisional-indonesia-bisa-dipadukan-dengan-kesenian-jepang-loh/attachment/taiko-4/\" data-orig-file=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/taiko-4.jpg\" data-orig-size=\"608,320\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;4&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;FinePixS2Pro&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;1048868509&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;17&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;800&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0.00285714285714&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"(Sumber : CIAYO Pictures)\" data-image-description=\"&lt;p&gt;(Sumber : CIAYO Pictures)&lt;/p&gt;\n\" data-medium-file=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/taiko-4-300x158.jpg\" data-large-file=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/taiko-4.jpg\" class=\"size-full wp-image-41739\" src=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/taiko-4.jpg\" alt=\"(Sumber : CIAYO Pictures)\" width=\"608\" height=\"320\" srcset=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/taiko-4.jpg 608w, https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/taiko-4-300x158.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 608px) 100vw, 608px\" /><p id=\"caption-attachment-41739\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Sumber : CIAYO Pictures</p></div>\n<p>Acara yang berlangsung selama 2 hari ini menampilkan berbagai seni dari Jepang, seperti di awal acara yang menampilkan <em>Taiko Performance</em>. Bro sis yang lihat penampilan Taiko Okinawa kemarin pasti melihat sesuatu yang unik, karena mereka menari sambil menabuh sebuah drum besar dan kecil. Nah, drum yang mereka bawa itu bernama “Taiko”. Taiko sendiri merupakan sebuah alat musik tradisional Jepang yang berbentuk seperti drum. Hm, mungkin kalau di Indonesia terlihat seperti bedug atau gendang, ya. Jika diartikan dalam bahasa Inggris, Taiko berarti “Fat Drums”. (Ya, ampun, benda aja dikatain, ya.)</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_41745\" style=\"width: 618px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-41745\" data-attachment-id=\"41745\" data-permalink=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/news/ternyata-musik-tradisional-indonesia-bisa-dipadukan-dengan-kesenian-jepang-loh/attachment/taiko6/\" data-orig-file=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/taiko6.jpg\" data-orig-size=\"608,320\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;4&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;FinePixS2Pro&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;1048868509&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;17&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;800&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0.00285714285714&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"Sumber : wikipedia.org\" data-image-description=\"&lt;p&gt;Sumber : wikipedia.org&lt;/p&gt;\n\" data-medium-file=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/taiko6-300x158.jpg\" data-large-file=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/taiko6.jpg\" class=\"size-full wp-image-41745\" src=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/taiko6.jpg\" alt=\"Sumber : wikipedia.org\" width=\"608\" height=\"320\" srcset=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/taiko6.jpg 608w, https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/taiko6-300x158.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 608px) 100vw, 608px\" /><p id=\"caption-attachment-41745\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Sumber : wikipedia.org</p></div>\n<p>Taiko sudah digunakan di Jepang lebih dari 2000 tahun yang lalu. Menurut beberapa penelitian arkeologi dan antropologi, orang-orang kuno di Era Jyomon sudah menggunakan drum sebagai alat komunikasi atau alat untuk ritual keagamaan. Pada masa Feodal di Jepang, taiko sering digunakan untuk memotivasi pasukan, menolong menentukan langkah barisan, dan mengatur perintah atau pengumuman.</p>\n<p>Menjelang atau pada saat akan memasuki pertempuran, <em>taiko yaku</em> (penabuh drum) bertanggung jawab untuk menentukan langkah barisan, biasanya dengan enam langkah untuk setiap pukulan drum (ketukan-2-3-4-5-6, ketukan-2-3-4-5-6). Menurut salah satu catatan sejarah (<em>Gunji Yoshu</em>), sembilan rangkai dari lima ketukan berarti memanggil sekutu ke medan tempur, sementara sembilan rangkai dari tiga ketukan, yang dipercepat tiga atau empat kalinya, adalah panggilan untuk maju dan mengejar lawan. Agak ribet, ya?</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_41740\" style=\"width: 618px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-41740\" data-attachment-id=\"41740\" data-permalink=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/news/ternyata-musik-tradisional-indonesia-bisa-dipadukan-dengan-kesenian-jepang-loh/attachment/taiko1/\" data-orig-file=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/taiko1.jpg\" data-orig-size=\"608,320\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;4&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;FinePixS2Pro&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;1048868509&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;17&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;800&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0.00285714285714&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"Sumber : japansocietyboston.org\" data-image-description=\"&lt;p&gt;Sumber : japansocietyboston.org&lt;/p&gt;\n\" data-medium-file=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/taiko1-300x158.jpg\" data-large-file=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/taiko1.jpg\" class=\"size-full wp-image-41740\" src=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/taiko1.jpg\" alt=\"Sumber : japansocietyboston.org\" width=\"608\" height=\"320\" srcset=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/taiko1.jpg 608w, https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/taiko1-300x158.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 608px) 100vw, 608px\" /><p id=\"caption-attachment-41740\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Sumber : japansocietyboston.org</p></div>\n<p>Seiring perkembangan jaman, taiko berubah menjadi seni kontemporer dalam menabuh drum di berbagai <em>event</em> atau acara tertentu di Jepang, dengan menggunakan berbagai ukuran dan jenis drum, dari ukuran yang paling besar hingga yang mudah dibawa oleh tangan.</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_41743\" style=\"width: 618px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-41743\" data-attachment-id=\"41743\" data-permalink=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/news/ternyata-musik-tradisional-indonesia-bisa-dipadukan-dengan-kesenian-jepang-loh/attachment/taiko5/\" data-orig-file=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/taiko5.jpg\" data-orig-size=\"608,320\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;4&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;FinePixS2Pro&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;1048868509&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;17&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;800&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0.00285714285714&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"Sumber : CIAYO Pictures\" data-image-description=\"&lt;p&gt;Sumber : CIAYO Pictures&lt;/p&gt;\n\" data-medium-file=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/taiko5-300x158.jpg\" data-large-file=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/taiko5.jpg\" class=\"size-full wp-image-41743\" src=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/taiko5.jpg\" alt=\"Sumber : CIAYO Pictures\" width=\"608\" height=\"320\" srcset=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/taiko5.jpg 608w, https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/taiko5-300x158.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 608px) 100vw, 608px\" /><p id=\"caption-attachment-41743\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Sumber : CIAYO Pictures</p></div>\n<p>Saat acara Bonenkai kemarin, ada yang menarik dari penampilan Taiko Okinawa ini. Penampilan tarian Taiko kemarin menyelipkan beberapa lagu daerah Indonesia sebagai pengiring penampilan tarian mereka. Lagu-lagu daerah yang mereka pakai antara lain adalah lagu dari daerah Jawa Barat, Bali, Sulawesi, dan lainnya.</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_41741\" style=\"width: 618px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-41741\" data-attachment-id=\"41741\" data-permalink=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/news/ternyata-musik-tradisional-indonesia-bisa-dipadukan-dengan-kesenian-jepang-loh/attachment/taiko2/\" data-orig-file=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/taiko2.jpg\" data-orig-size=\"608,320\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;4&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;FinePixS2Pro&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;1048868509&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;17&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;800&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0.00285714285714&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"Sumber : CIAYO Pictures\" data-image-description=\"&lt;p&gt;Sumber : CIAYO Pictures&lt;/p&gt;\n\" data-medium-file=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/taiko2-300x158.jpg\" data-large-file=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/taiko2.jpg\" class=\"size-full wp-image-41741\" src=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/taiko2.jpg\" alt=\"Sumber : CIAYO Pictures\" width=\"608\" height=\"320\" srcset=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/taiko2.jpg 608w, https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/taiko2-300x158.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 608px) 100vw, 608px\" /><p id=\"caption-attachment-41741\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Sumber : CIAYO Pictures</p></div>\n<p>Taiko Okinawa membuktikan bahwa budaya Indonesia bisa dipadu-padankan dengan budaya Jepang. Keren banget, ya bro sis. Hal ini membuktikan walaupun kamu sangat menyukai budaya luar, tapi tetap tidak boleh lupa sama budaya sendiri. Masa punya orang disayang, punya sendiri dibiarkan? Hehe.</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_41742\" style=\"width: 618px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-41742\" data-attachment-id=\"41742\" data-permalink=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/news/ternyata-musik-tradisional-indonesia-bisa-dipadukan-dengan-kesenian-jepang-loh/attachment/taiko3/\" data-orig-file=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/taiko3.jpg\" data-orig-size=\"608,320\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;4&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;FinePixS2Pro&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;1048868509&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;17&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;800&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0.00285714285714&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"Sumber : CIAYO Pictures\" data-image-description=\"&lt;p&gt;Sumber : CIAYO Pictures&lt;/p&gt;\n\" data-medium-file=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/taiko3-300x158.jpg\" data-large-file=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/taiko3.jpg\" class=\"size-full wp-image-41742\" src=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/taiko3.jpg\" alt=\"Sumber : CIAYO Pictures\" width=\"608\" height=\"320\" srcset=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/taiko3.jpg 608w, https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/taiko3-300x158.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 608px) 100vw, 608px\" /><p id=\"caption-attachment-41742\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Sumber : CIAYO Pictures</p></div>\n<p>Selain itu, di akhir penampilannya penari taiko juga mengajak pengunjung acara Bonenkai Festival 12th untuk menari bersama-sama dengan mereka.</p>\n"}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"id":"5ddaab69-03fe-570a-82e0-36588b92e36c"}}}